2. all of 'damage' may be ancient. There are some slightly rounded ground facets on the blade edge (see drawing) up to c. 1mm across. On the assumption that these were put on as part of a resharpening process (not completed), the dashed line is a suggestion of the blade shape before the 'damage'. All blade measurements are taken, when affected, from this dashed line. The ground facets do not fill in a straight line, as would probably have been the case if this piece once had a continuous rounded blade edge. No striations are visible to the naked eye.
